==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Huntsman
<hw>Hunts"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Huntsmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
hunts, or who practices hunting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The person whose office it is to manage the chase or
to look after the hounds.</def> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Huntsman's cup</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the
sidesaddle flower, or common American pitcher plant (<spn>Sarracenia
purpurea</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 714 --></p>

<p><ent>Huntsmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
